Description:
The OptiCrop Smart Agricultural Production Optimization System is designed to analyze agricultural and environmental data and provide accurate crop recommendations to farmers and agricultural stakeholders. The application processes important soil and climate parameters such as Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), Potassium (K), temperature, humidity, rainfall, pH value, and seasonal conditions to determine the most suitable crop for cultivation.
The system provides a simple, responsive, and user-friendly web interface where users can easily enter agricultural data and receive real-time crop prediction results. It ensures smooth integration between the machine learning model and the web application to deliver fast, reliable, and accurate recommendations.
The application supports multiple machine learning algorithms, including K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN), Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, and K-Means Clustering, for model training and evaluation. It also includes data preprocessing, feature scaling, model evaluation, and prediction functionalities to improve overall performance and accuracy.
Additionally, the platform helps optimize the usage of water, fertilizers, and soil nutrients while reducing the risk of crop failure caused by unsuitable crop selection and changing environmental conditions. The system is designed to be scalable, reliable, and flexible, allowing future enhancements such as advanced predictive models, larger agricultural datasets, cloud deployment, and smart farming integration.
